#: src/dev-containers.md:1
msgid "Dev Containers"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:3
msgid ""
"Dev Containers provide a consistent, reproducible development environment by "
"defining your project's dependencies, tools, and settings in a container "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:5
msgid ""
"If your repository includes a `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` file, Zed "
"can open a project inside a development container."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:7
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:9
msgid ""
"Docker must be installed and available in your `PATH`. Zed requires the "
"`docker` command to be present. If you use Podman, you can alias it to "
"`docker` (e.g., `alias docker=podman`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:10
msgid ""
"Your project must contain a `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` directory/file."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:12
msgid "Using Dev Containers in Zed"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:14
msgid "Automatic prompt"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:16
msgid ""
"When you open a project that contains the `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` "
"directory/file, Zed will display a prompt asking whether to open the project "
"inside the dev container. Choosing \"Open in Container\" will:"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:18
msgid "Build the dev container image (if needed)."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:19
msgid "Launch the container."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:20
msgid "Reopen the project connected to the container environment."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:22
msgid "Manual open"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:24
msgid ""
"If you dismiss the prompt or want to reopen the project inside a container "
"later, you can use Zed's command palette to run the \"Project: Open Remote\" "
"command and select the option to open the project in a dev container. "
"Alternatively, you can reach for the Remote Projects modal (through the <kbd "
"class=\"keybinding\">ctrl-cmd-shift-o|alt-ctrl-shift-o</kbd> binding) and "
"choose the \"Connect Dev Container\" option."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:27
msgid "Editing the dev container configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:29
msgid ""
"If you modify `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json`, Zed does not currently "
"rebuild or reload the container automatically. After changing configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:31
msgid ""
"Stop or kill the existing container manually (e.g., via `docker kill "
"<container>`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:32
msgid "Reopen the project in the container."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:34
msgid "Working in a Dev Container"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:36
msgid ""
"Once connected, Zed operates inside the container environment for tasks, "
"terminals, and language servers. Files are linked from your workspace into "
"the container according to the dev container specification."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:39
msgid "Known Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:41
msgid "**Note:** This feature is still in development."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:43
msgid ""
"**Extensions:** Zed does not yet manage extensions separately for container "
"environments. The host's extensions are used as-is."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:44
msgid ""
"**Port forwarding:** Only the `appPort` field is supported. `forwardPorts` "
"and other advanced port-forwarding features are not implemented."
msgstr ""

#: src/dev-containers.md:45
msgid ""
"**Configuration changes:** Updates to `devcontainer.json` do not trigger "
"automatic rebuilds or reloads; containers must be manually restarted."
msgstr ""

